<section xml:id="sec_tenth-examplesB" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Examples B</title>
  
<paragraphs>
  <title>KTG</title>
  
  <example>
    <statement>
      <p>
        The rms speed of <m> H_{2} </m> molecules is 1.84 km/sec. What will be the rms 
        speed of <m>O_{2} </m> molecules at the same temperature? The molecular weights of 
        hydrogen and oxygen are 2 and 32 respectively.
      </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
      <p>
        We know that 
        <me>
          v_{rms} = \sqrt{\frac{3RT}{M}} 
        </me>
       <me>
        \text{or,}\quad \frac{(v_{rms})_{O}}{(v_{rms})_{H}} = \sqrt{\frac{M_{H}}{M_{O}}} 
       </me>
       <me>
        \therefore\quad (v_{rms})_{O} = (v_{rms})_{H}\times  \sqrt{\frac{M_{H}}{M_{O}}} =(1.84 km/s)\times \sqrt{\frac{2}{32}} =0.459 \,km/s.
       </me>
             </p>
    </solution>
  </example>


 <example>
  <statement>
    <p>
      At what temperature does the kinetic energy of an atom be 1.0 eV? <m>(k_{B}=1.38\times 10^{-23} \,J/K)</m>.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      Average kinetic energy <m>e_{k}</m> of an atom is given by 
      <me>
        \frac{1}{2}mv_{rms}^{2}=\frac{f}{2}k_{B}T = \frac{3}{2}k_{B}T 
      </me>
      <m>\because f=3</m> for a monoatomic molecule
<me>
  \therefore\quad T = \frac{2}{3}\frac{e_{k}}{k_{B}}
</me>
<me>
  = \frac{2}{3}\left(\frac{1.0\, eV\times 1.60\times 10^{-19} \,J/eV}{1.38\times 10^{-23} \,J/K}\right)= 7.729\times 10^{3} \,K
</me>
    </p>
  </solution>
 </example>


 <example>
  <statement>
    <p>
      At what temperature will the rms velocity of hydrogen molecules has double of its value at NTP, if pressure remains constant.
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      We have -
      <me>
        v_{rms}=\sqrt{\frac{3k_{B}T}{m}}
      </me>
            At  NTP, <m>T=0^{o}C=273 \,K</m>.
            <me>
              (v_{rms})_{1}=v_{rms}=\sqrt{\frac{3k_{B}\times 273}{m}}
            </me>
                 At  NTP, <m>T=T \,K</m>
                 <me>
                  (v_{rms})_{2}=2v_{rms} = \sqrt{\frac{3k_{B}\times T}{m}}
                 </me>
                 <me>
                  \text{or,}\quad  2v_{rms} =\sqrt{\frac{3k_{B}\times T}{m}} = 2\sqrt{\frac{3k_{B}\times 273}{m}}
                 </me>
                 <me>
                  \text{or,}\quad  \frac{T}{273} = 4
                 </me>
                 <me>
                  \therefore\quad  T = 4\times 273=1092 \,K = 819 \,^{o}C
                 </me>
       </p>
  </solution>
 </example>
</paragraphs>
 
